This workflow is based on the FeatureFinderIdentification approach published in Weisser et al., 2017. It's supposed to be
superior to conventional feature finding by matching all (consensus) identifications to features in all runs. It is a feature
propagation algorithm just like DemixQ. Essential steps:
- RT normalize mzML runs before searching using e.g. MapAlignerPoseClustering/MapAlingerIdentification
- merge all identifications from all runs using IDmerger
